\section{Fits}
\label{app:fits}

The parameters for the gap fits of Eq.~(\ref{eq:gapfit}) in Tables~\ref{table:1S0} and \ref{table:3PF2} have been obtained from a robust bisquare non-linear least-square fit. The function is fit to all non-zero gap data plus the first zero value after the gap closure. For singlet gaps, in addition to the data points of Fig.~\ref{fig:gap1s0}, we have supplemented the fit with a point with zero gap at zero Fermi momentum. Other than the N3LO results, the fitting algorithm prefers a gap opening at $k_0=0.04-0.05$ fm$^{-1}$. No additional points were given in the triplet channel. The goodness of fit as measured by the $r^2$ coefficient of determination, which is above $0.99$ for singlet fits. Triplet fits, in contrast, have $r^2$ ranging between $0.76$ for CDBonn, $0.83$ for Av18 and $0.97$ for N3LO. 

